<paragraph id="E26BFB451834B58C0D85AE2E73D48EA2" pageId="null" pageNumber="399">Kaltes Fingerkraut</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</title>
<subSubSection id="A309A0D505D74663B81FFB215A4DF915" pageId="null" pageNumber="399" type="description">
<paragraph id="868CD4D6EB56CE826B87C8C01E6282A3" pageId="null" pageNumber="399">
Unterscheidet sich von 
<taxonomicName id="A9640B2210A90B6F7A6CC6AD9F7DF71C" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Potentilla" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="null" pageNumber="399" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dubia">
<emphasis id="50B570BFA4B6A57BD41BF761E1EDFAF1" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="399">P. dubia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 23) durch folgende Merkmale: 
<normalizedToken id="CF2E840EE33F69193DC75380A5AD77E4" originalValue="Graugrün" pageId="null" pageNumber="399">Graugruen</normalizedToken>
, 
<emphasis id="BED63F56C2916EAFE689D8379AEF6F82" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="399">ganze Pflanze</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="28FDC8969F35A38617BDFFAC942DDF2F" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="399">auch Blattoberseite</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="70B453C029150AE072DFC0BE76F449E6" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="399">
mit 
<normalizedToken id="3783A6BF0AD83A50852ED991F5AD2BF0" originalValue="±" pageId="null" pageNumber="399">+/-</normalizedToken>
geraden Haaren besetzt und deshalb seidig 
<normalizedToken id="FF3478E2616508D6789856BC4E0B152A" originalValue="glänzend" pageId="null" pageNumber="399">glaenzend</normalizedToken>
; 
<normalizedToken id="FEF4B99D1ED3246B50BBFEFD60F766B5" originalValue="überall" pageId="null" pageNumber="399">ueberall</normalizedToken>
zwischen den Haaren zahlreiche, 0,05-0,1 mm lange, kopfige, gelbliche 
<normalizedToken id="7D1AA4B4E13045E9720B89D67A0BB908" originalValue="Drüsen" pageId="null" pageNumber="399">Druesen</normalizedToken>
.
</emphasis>
- 
<normalizedToken id="025D6C399AEF078E28614D770600BFDA" originalValue="Blüte" pageId="null" pageNumber="399">Bluete</normalizedToken>
: Sommer.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E63D2AFDA7DDF682817D5ECB48A91956" pageId="null" pageNumber="399">
<emphasis id="07F3C4598EEE5415174BF4A7DC48D67A" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="399">Zytologische Angaben. 2n</emphasis>
= 
<emphasis id="022D506CBE4D1FAA54ED3D51656AB2B9" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="399">28:</emphasis>
Material aus dem Wallis (Grandes Autannes) (Favarger 1959).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CB56B63304706E7658DBBBED6F93E121" pageId="null" pageNumber="399">
<emphasis id="7F501F1E662BCA99D599B196D8610DA2" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="399">Standort.</emphasis>
Alpin. Trockene, humusreiche, kalk- und 
<normalizedToken id="02C201FF36F24F2C39E10C0E87F3B14D" originalValue="nährstoffarme" pageId="null" pageNumber="399">naehrstoffarme</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="4B6F9D7F05D67B49F82ED26876C02088" originalValue="Böden" pageId="null" pageNumber="399">Boeden</normalizedToken>
an windexponierten 
<normalizedToken id="5C3ADC6C06E04232FD0E0E0F2A25CAA9" originalValue="Hängen" pageId="null" pageNumber="399">Haengen</normalizedToken>
und Graten. In 2 Subassoziationen des 
<emphasis id="6EBEC8951DDDB31042B1BD01E24BFA67" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="399">Caricetum curvulae</emphasis>
Brockmann-Jerosch 1907: 
<emphasis id="57A9E2FE94BDAEFBF78F7033AD480710" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="399">elynetosum</emphasis>
Br.-Bl. 1926 und 
<emphasis id="EE4CF2ADD5108838DD1ED76F74884E86" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="399">cetrarietosum</emphasis>
Br.-Bl. 1926.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="22EE1D4C315711EB5AEDA218E2DF8056" pageId="null" pageNumber="399">
<emphasis id="7AF4676CE81F9B9F41B3CAACB2DBBA82" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="399">
Verbreitung. 
<normalizedToken id="DCE30C22101D9062610D98FB8E31B8CD" originalValue="Alpin-pyrenäische" pageId="null" pageNumber="399">Alpin-pyrenaeische</normalizedToken>
Pflanze:
</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="F1BD764309D7F55FE1FC65522864DF95" originalValue="Hochpyrenäen" pageId="null" pageNumber="399">Hochpyrenaeen</normalizedToken>
, Alpen (von der 
<normalizedToken id="E4590788687AD036CF766D24A7F33B99" originalValue="Dauphiné" pageId="null" pageNumber="399">Dauphine</normalizedToken>
bis Steiermark). - Im Gebiet durch die Alpen verbreitet, nicht 
<normalizedToken id="F2A7444900EC916F5583D7F1C2BAA82D" originalValue="häufig" pageId="null" pageNumber="399">haeufig</normalizedToken>
, in den Nordalpen selten.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="18026CAFF34DFBC906C0616C2B4D2DC1" pageId="null" pageNumber="399">
<emphasis id="12FA06791058A554E744FC170E7852BB" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="399">
Bemerkungen. 
<taxonomicName id="2C525CC0F1741B8A133C25F269318904" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Potentilla" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="null" pageNumber="399" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="frigida">P. frigida</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
ist nicht vielgestaltig.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
